      <h2>"Little Women" (1994)</h2>
      <p> <a href="https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0110367/">Little Women</a>, directed by Gillian Armstrong, is a heartfelt and visually elegant adaptation of Little Women by Louisa May Alcott. Set during and after the American Civil War, the film follows the four March sisters—Meg, Jo, Beth, and Amy—as they navigate love, ambition, loss, and the expectations placed upon women in 19th-century America.</p>
