    <h2>"It's A Wonderful Life" (1946)</h2>
     <p><a href="https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0038650/">It's a Wonderful Life</a>, directed by Frank Capra, is one of cinema’s most enduring holiday classics. Though initially met with modest success upon release, it has since become a beloved staple of the season—a film that blends sentiment, fantasy, and social commentary into a deeply moving portrait of one man’s life.</p>
